Joseph MALNAR, Anthony D. Fiar and Matt Kozuh v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 4850. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. Sept. 22, 1932. Dwight H. Green, U. S. Atty., of Chicago, Ill.

Before ALSCHULER and SPARKS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for appellee, it is now here ordered and adjudged that this cause be docketed in this court, and that this appeal he, and the same is hereby, dismissed pursuant to section 1 of rule 14 of the Rules of this court. It is further ordered that the mandate issue forthwith.
